        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">The approximate global melamine production is reported by the OECD (1998)  to be 600000 metric tonnes per year, supplied by about 30 producers. 250000 metric tonnes are said to be used in Europe. 

Reference(s):
OECD. 1998. Screening Information Dataset, Initial Assessment Report for the 8th SIAM, Melamine. pp. 119. Retreived online from http://www.inchem.org/documents/sids/sids/108781.pdf, 5 July 2017.</productionVolumeComment>
